ing his contribution to British television. Engaging with thematic and ideological notions of the personal, the autobiographical, the honest, the shameless, the pleasurable and the painful recourse of the specificity of ‘ordinary life’, the volume seeks to combine close textual analysis of Abbott’s work with archival research and specially commissioned interviews with Abbott and other important industry practitioners.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aTelevision producers and directorszGreat BritainvBiography. 0aTelevision writerszGreat BritainvBiography. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2021. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Television / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  a2004 British Academy Television Awards.  aAbbottVision.  aBritish television.  aChildren's Ward.  aCoronation Street.  aCracker.  aEnglish Mackintosh Textiles factory.  aLinda Green.  aPaul Abbott.  aShameless.  aState of Play.  apolitical television.  atelevision drama.  atelevision producer.  atelevision screenwriter.  atelevisual case studies.1 aJohnson, Beth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611167840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526111678423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526111678/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles